From a1b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: removed for privacy
Date: Thu, 27 Feb 2026 10:00:00 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] platform/surface: Add s2idle/hibernate fix v5.6 for Surface
 Laptop 5

INTC1055 pinctrl power-gating during s2idle corrupts pin 213's PADCFG0
RXINV bit. The flipped bit fires a spurious SCI on GPE 0x52. In the
kernel's s2idle wake path, acpi_ec_dispatch_gpe() calls
acpi_any_gpe_status_set() which promotes any non-EC GPE with status set
to a full resume. The corrupted pin causes level-like re-assertion,
so the status bit is always set when checked. The system either never
wakes (wakeup framework poisoned) or wakes spuriously on every s2idle
cycle.

Fix by intercepting in the ACPI wakeup handler, which runs before
acpi_ec_dispatch_gpe(). The handler repairs PADCFG RXINV corruption
and clears GPE 0x52 status, preventing spurious full resume promotion.
The actual lid-open decision is deferred to an LPS0 check callback
which reads RXSTATE directly. Additional layers handle post-resume
failsafe re-suspend, lid close detection via RXSTATE polling, and
exponential backoff to prevent sleep-wake storms.

SW_LID input events are emitted for lid open/close so userspace (logind,
GNOME, KDE) can apply its own lid policy. The module does not call
pm_suspend() on lid close; suspend policy is left to the desktop
environment.

v5.4 changes: GPE 0x52 kept masked during s2idle (VNN RXSTATE glitches
fired as SCI causing spurious full wakes). Use acpi_enable_gpe instead
of acpi_set_gpe to fix reference count imbalance that left GPE disabled
after first suspend cycle. Clear stale GPE status before unmask and
delay unmask from resume_early to PM_POST_SUSPEND to prevent false lid
events to logind. Full PADCFG0 comparison (not just RXINV) to catch all
VNN corruption. Extended GPIORXDIS toggle to 1ms with 15s RXSTATE
settling guard. lock_sessions changed to UMH_WAIT_PROC with 500ms
delay before failsafe re-suspend to let GNOME render lock screen.
lps0_prepare refreshes golden snapshot via save_all_pins to capture
ACPI's legitimate RXINV changes.

v5.6 changes: capture ACPI button driver input device via input_handler,
silently set SW_LID=1 before suspend, send real SW_LID=0 on event0 in
PM_POST_SUSPEND for GNOME display wake, KEY_WAKEUP to unblank lock
screen. VNN stale latch: GPIORXDIS toggle in poller when RXSTATE stuck
at 0 past settle window. Remove ULID call from lid_close_fn (ghost
suspend source).

Link: https://github.com/linux-surface/linux-surface/issues/1782
Signed-off-by: removed for privacy
Patchset: surface-s2idle-fix
